{
  "texts": [
    "In the case of the quadratic loss, we have (Audibert, 2004, page 22).",
    "A similar idea was used later beyond regression to control (Germain et al., 2015; Masegosa, 2020).",
    "However, note that in the case of classification, f θ (x) ∈ {0, 1} for any x and θ, but fρ λ (x) can be any value in [0, 1].",
    "We can define a new classifier by f maj ρλ (x) = 1 if fρ λ (x) ≥ 1/2 and f maj ρλ (x) = 0 otherwise.",
    "This is known as the weighted majority vote classifier."
  ]
}